column1: A total of 496 GST - Nedd8 modified and associated proteins have been identified, including all of the eight cullin family members ( i. e., Cul - 1, - 2, - 3, - 4A, - 4B, - 5, - 7, and Parc) that are involved in the neddylation and ubiquitin - proteasome degradation pathway.

These two forms of recombinant beta1 gamma1 and retinal beta1 gamma1 were different in their abilities to associate with rod outer segment membranes with the following rank order: beta1 gamma1S74L > beta1 gamma1WT > retinal beta1 gamma1.

The influence of insulin on this pathway consists of five important events: ( 1) p21Ras activation is promoted by insulin stimulation of the guanine nucleotide exchange factor, Sos, resulting in increased GTP - loading of p21Ras; ( 2) p21Ras deactivation involves the hyperphosphorylation of Sos; ( 3) insulin increases farnesyltransferase ( FTase) activity that farnesylates p21Ras; ( 4) increased amounts of farnesylated p21Ras translocate to the plasma membrane where they can be activated by other growth - promoting agents; and ( 5) cellular responses to other growth factors are potentiated by insulin - stimulated pre - loading of the plasma membrane with farnesylated p21Ras.
